                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Lord
                        Lyons</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-12-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 16, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord</hi>: This department is in possession of authentic
                    information that among the persons who recently committed piracy and murder on
                    board the United States steamer Chesapeake were two named Braine and Parr,
                    respectively, and that they have taken refuge in the British province of New
                    Brunswick or Nova Scotia. As it is desirable that they should be detained there
                    until the formal affidavits can be forwarded with a view to their extradition
                    for trial in this country, I will thank you to request her Majesty’s authorities
                    to do anything which can be legally done for that purpose.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, with high consideration, my lord, your obedient
                    servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD. </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Right Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lord Lyons,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
